<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,926,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,926,952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Description</emphasis>
. Body robust, medium to small size (
<figureCitation box="[701,777,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[790,864,926,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,184,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov. 25. Female body, lateral view; 26. Male body, lateral view; 27. The same, frontal view; 28. The same, dorsal view; 29.Apex of female abdomen, lateral view; 30. Apex of male abdomen, dorsal view; 31. Female head and sternal plate, ventral view; 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view; 33. The same, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756029/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">25–28</figureCitation>
). Head rugose, considerably shorter than pronotum. Face in profile reclinated; frontal ridge below the antennal bases straight (
<figureCitation box="[981,1087,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Figs. 4, 8</figureCitation>
) or excised (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1300,963,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Fastigium of vertex triangular, deeply sulcate and projecting forward at the distance less than the half of eye length; lateral margins bordered by low carinulae reaching apical margin of the compound eyes; foveolae shallow, short triangular. Vertex between eyes considerably narrower than an eye (
<figureCitation box="[805,875,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Eyes large, oval. Frontal ridge distinct, sulcate, with margins almost parallel (
<figureCitation box="[489,597,1106,1133]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Figs. 3, 5</figureCitation>
) or narrowed between antennal bases (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1125,1107,1133]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,184,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov. 25. Female body, lateral view; 26. Male body, lateral view; 27. The same, frontal view; 28. The same, dorsal view; 29.Apex of female abdomen, lateral view; 30. Apex of male abdomen, dorsal view; 31. Female head and sternal plate, ventral view; 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view; 33. The same, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756029/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Antennae filiform. Pronotum rugose, crossed by three transverse furrows; prozona distinctly longer than metazona; median carina vestigial; lateral carinae absent; anterior margin of prozona almost straight; posterior margin of metazona triangularly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[159,239,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Figs. 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[252,284,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,184,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov. 25. Female body, lateral view; 26. Male body, lateral view; 27. The same, frontal view; 28. The same, dorsal view; 29.Apex of female abdomen, lateral view; 30. Apex of male abdomen, dorsal view; 31. Female head and sternal plate, ventral view; 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view; 33. The same, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756029/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">28</figureCitation>
). Prosternal spine short, straight, conical, with broad base and pointed apex. Mesosternal lobes widely separated, subsquare or trapezoidal; mesosternal interspace transverse; metasternal lobes widely separated (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,184,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov. 25. Female body, lateral view; 26. Male body, lateral view; 27. The same, frontal view; 28. The same, dorsal view; 29.Apex of female abdomen, lateral view; 30. Apex of male abdomen, dorsal view; 31. Female head and sternal plate, ventral view; 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view; 33. The same, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756029/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Tegmina and hind wings always present; apterous forms unknown. Hind femora stout; both dorsal and ventral median carinae finely serrated; dorso-median carina terminating in a small tooth; ventral genicular lobes of hind knee with distinct apical spine (
<figureCitation box="[507,589,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) or narrowly rounded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[928,1008,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Hind tibiae not apically expanded but provided by weakly keeled margins; outer apical dorsal spine small. Hind tarsi short, not longer than the half of hind tibiae; third segment (without claws) as long as two others together or slightly shorter; arolium large, reaching the middle or apex of claws. Tympanum large, oval. Male 10th abdominal tergite with distinct furculae or without it; supra-anal plate triangular, trapezoidal or long-oval, with a median basal impression; cerci compressed, short, conical, with pointed or blunt apex, unarmed or provided by tooth on the inner side; subgenital plate short (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Figs. 10, 11. 13</figureCitation>
). Female supra-anal plate elongated, triangular, with a median basal impression; cerci conical with pointed apex; subgenital plate with long triangle pointed apex; basivalvular plates wide (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1075,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor short or elongated; dorsal valves shorter than lower ones, widened apically, dentate only at apex; ventral valves slightly curved and also dentate or crenulate at apex only (
<figureCitation box="[519,585,1683,1710]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia: epiphallus bridge-shaped, asymmetrical; bridge completely divided; left part of epiphallus larger what right one; oval sclerite present (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1195,1718,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1734,1758]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,316,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-80@8.[151,1436,308,1710]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Male genitalia of the subfamily Incolacridinae (15–18 after Hollis, 1975 and 19–24 after Ingrisch, 1989). 15. Incolacris trifasciata, epiphallus, dorsal view; 16. The same, Stolzia javana; 17. The same, Stolzia aberrans; 18. The same, Stolzia fasciata; 19–21. Bettotania maculata: 19. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 20. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), dorsal view; 21. The same, lateral view; 22–24. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov.: 22. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 23. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), lateral view; 24. The same, dorsal view. (Ae—ancorae; An—anterior projections of epiphallus; Ap—apical valves of penis; Apd—apodemes; Bp—basal valves of penis; Br—bridge; Cv—valves of cingulum; Fx—flexure; Lel—left lophi of epiphallus; Ler—right lophi of epiphallus; Os—oval sclerites; Rm—rami of cingulum; Sh—ectophallic sheath of penis; Zyg—zygoma)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756023/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Figs. 15–19, 22</figureCitation>
); valves of cingulum varied from long and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[488,570,1755,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1734,1758]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,316,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-80@8.[151,1436,308,1710]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Male genitalia of the subfamily Incolacridinae (15–18 after Hollis, 1975 and 19–24 after Ingrisch, 1989). 15. Incolacris trifasciata, epiphallus, dorsal view; 16. The same, Stolzia javana; 17. The same, Stolzia aberrans; 18. The same, Stolzia fasciata; 19–21. Bettotania maculata: 19. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 20. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), dorsal view; 21. The same, lateral view; 22–24. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov.: 22. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 23. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), lateral view; 24. The same, dorsal view. (Ae—ancorae; An—anterior projections of epiphallus; Ap—apical valves of penis; Apd—apodemes; Bp—basal valves of penis; Br—bridge; Cv—valves of cingulum; Fx—flexure; Lel—left lophi of epiphallus; Ler—right lophi of epiphallus; Os—oval sclerites; Rm—rami of cingulum; Sh—ectophallic sheath of penis; Zyg—zygoma)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756023/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) to short and stout (
<figureCitation box="[794,877,1755,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1734,1758]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,316,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-80@8.[151,1436,308,1710]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Male genitalia of the subfamily Incolacridinae (15–18 after Hollis, 1975 and 19–24 after Ingrisch, 1989). 15. Incolacris trifasciata, epiphallus, dorsal view; 16. The same, Stolzia javana; 17. The same, Stolzia aberrans; 18. The same, Stolzia fasciata; 19–21. Bettotania maculata: 19. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 20. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), dorsal view; 21. The same, lateral view; 22–24. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov.: 22. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 23. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), lateral view; 24. The same, dorsal view. (Ae—ancorae; An—anterior projections of epiphallus; Ap—apical valves of penis; Apd—apodemes; Bp—basal valves of penis; Br—bridge; Cv—valves of cingulum; Fx—flexure; Lel—left lophi of epiphallus; Ler—right lophi of epiphallus; Os—oval sclerites; Rm—rami of cingulum; Sh—ectophallic sheath of penis; Zyg—zygoma)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756023/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
); apical valves of penis conical or lobe-like; basal valves of penis connected with apical ones by unbroken flexure (
<figureCitation box="[866,958,1791,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1734,1758]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,316,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-80@8.[151,1436,308,1710]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Male genitalia of the subfamily Incolacridinae (15–18 after Hollis, 1975 and 19–24 after Ingrisch, 1989). 15. Incolacris trifasciata, epiphallus, dorsal view; 16. The same, Stolzia javana; 17. The same, Stolzia aberrans; 18. The same, Stolzia fasciata; 19–21. Bettotania maculata: 19. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 20. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), dorsal view; 21. The same, lateral view; 22–24. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov.: 22. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 23. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), lateral view; 24. The same, dorsal view. (Ae—ancorae; An—anterior projections of epiphallus; Ap—apical valves of penis; Apd—apodemes; Bp—basal valves of penis; Br—bridge; Cv—valves of cingulum; Fx—flexure; Lel—left lophi of epiphallus; Ler—right lophi of epiphallus; Os—oval sclerites; Rm—rami of cingulum; Sh—ectophallic sheath of penis; Zyg—zygoma)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756023/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">Figs. 21</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[969,1000,1791,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,184,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-15@10.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov. 25. Female body, lateral view; 26. Male body, lateral view; 27. The same, frontal view; 28. The same, dorsal view; 29.Apex of female abdomen, lateral view; 30. Apex of male abdomen, dorsal view; 31. Female head and sternal plate, ventral view; 32. Male genitalia, dorsal view; 33. The same, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756029/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="107">33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
